Robert Dumitrescu - CSCI 4229 - HW6

Compile the program with the command: "make"

To run the program, use the command: "./hw5"

Mode can be switched with "m" | Modes cycle as followed: Orthogonal -> Perspective -> First Person
Spacebar can be used to toggle the automatic orbit of the light
Light height can be modified with "r" and "R"
Radius of the light's orbit can be modified with "v" and "V"
THe light can be manually moved along its orbit with "f" and "F"

The view can be rotated using the arrow keys
Eye position can be altered in first person mode with w, a, s, and d

This program is an extension of my hw5.

Total time taken: 8 hours